	UESP Game Map Wiki Extension
	============================
	by Dave Humphrey (dave@uesp.net)
	Released under the GPL v2

This is a MediaWiki extension for using the custom UESP game maps within a
wiki page. It requires the UESP map code to be installed and setup separately.

NOTE: This extension was developed specifically for the UESP site and may 
require modification to work in another site.



   Installation
-----------------------

   - If installing to the UESP servers run the deploy script from the source
     directory:
		uespdeploy

   - If installing on a non-UESP server can manually copy the files into the 
     new directory 'UespMap' in your MediaWiki /.extensions/ directory.

   - Add the following line in your LocalSettings.php file:
          require_once("$IP/extensions/UespMap/UespMap.php");


   Usage
-----------------------
Add a map onto a page using the custom '<uespmap>' tag. For detailed usage
and parameter descriptions see:
  
   http://www.uesp.net/wiki/UESPWiki:Extension_UespMap

